<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Resitivity.Guru</title>
  <link href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=News+Cycle|Fredericka+the+Great' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag    "application", "jquery-ui-1.10.4.custom.css", media: "all", "data-turbolinks-track" => true %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag "jquery-1.11.1.min.js", "jquery-ui-1.10.4.custom.min.js", "application.js", "data-turbolinks-track" => true %>
  <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
</head>
<body> 
  
    <div style="background-image:url('/assets/images/Resiguru.png');height:300px;">
        <h1 style="color:#fff;font-size:5em;margin:auto;padding: 50px 0px 0px 50px;">Resistivity.Guru</h1>
    </div>
 
    <div id="user_nav">
      <% if current_user %>
        <%= current_user.email %> | <%= link_to "Log out", logout_path %>
      <% else %>
        <%= link_to "Create Account", sign_up_path %>
      <% end %> 
    </div>
    <hr />  
    <h2 style="text-align:center;"><%= flash[:notice] %></h2>
    <%= yield %>
    <p style="width:45%;float:left;">Electrical resistance surveys, also called earth resistance or resistivity surveys, are one of a number of methods used in archaeological geophysics. In this type of survey electrical resistance meters are used to detect and map subsurface archaeological features and patterning. This site renders the data readings of these surveys into coloured maps.</p>
  </div>
</body>
</html>